    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Stores the default high-level tolerances used in idol.</para>
<para>It is possible for external-mip to have additional tolerance parameters, yet, the tolerances defined in this namespace should always be taken into account by the optimizer. Apart from the Sparsity tolerance, users can also change tolerance values at a local level (i.e., at an optimizer level) rather than at a global level. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
